criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  individuals diagnosed with chronic non-specific low back pain for a period of more
             than 3 months, without irradiation for lower limbs;

          -  who present pain intensity greater than 3 points in the Numerical Pain Scale;

          -  to sign the Free and Informed Consent Form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  BMI> 30;

          -  previous surgeries in the spine;

          -  severe spinal affection (tumors, infection, unconsolidated or vicious consolidation
             fractures, inflammatory diseases);

          -  rheumatic disease;

          -  contraindication to performing the exercises according to the American College of
             Sports Medicine Guidelines;

          -  degenerative or inflammatory joint and other body segments;

          -  patients who are in labor litigation;

          -  pregnancy;

          -  patients who are undergoing other type of physiotherapeutic or drug treatment.
